# --- Binaries & Compiled Files ---
# Go produces a single static binary. We don't want to commit it.
bin/
tmp/
dist/
# If you run `go build -o myapp`, ignore the resulting file
myapp

# --- Air (Live Reloading) ---
# Air builds your app into a temporary directory before running it.
.air*
tmp/

# --- Nix ---
# If you use direnv, it creates a local cache.
.direnv/
result
result-*

# --- Environment & Secrets ---
# Never, ever commit your actual .env file with DB passwords!
.env
*.env.local
!.env.example

# --- Go Dependencies ---
# Generally, we don't commit the vendor folder in modern Go (post-1.11)
vendor/

# --- Operating System Files ---
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db

# --- Database / Tools ---
# If you use go-migrate or local docker volumes
dump.sql